{"questionId":"14619718","questionHtml":"<p>Prove by mathematical induction that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; is divisible by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp;for all&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>base case&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp;so true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>assume true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;i.e.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;is divisible by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>The assumption of truth must be clear. Do not award the<em><strong> M1</strong></em> for statements such&nbsp;as \"let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>\" or \"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;is true\".&nbsp;Subsequent marks can still be awarded.</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>consider&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>M1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mn>25</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mn>17</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mn>8</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>25</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mn>25</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mn>17</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mn>17</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mn>17</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mn>17</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mn>17</mn></mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>25</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;which is divisible by 17&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>25</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> M1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>25</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>25</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>25</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math></em></strong></p>\n<p>hence for<strong><em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>25</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math></em></strong>&nbsp;is divisible by 17&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>since true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, and true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> implies true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, <br>therefore true for all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">z</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Only award <strong>R1</strong> if 4 of the previous 6 marks have been awarded<br><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>5</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;may be replaced by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>25</mn><mi>k</mi></msup></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>8</mn><mi>k</mi></msup></math> throughout.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[7 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14619718","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ1.6","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Prove by mathematical induction that 52n-23n is divisible by 17 for all n∈ℤ+.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"6","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}